Class CayleyDickson

java.lang.Object
CayleyDickson
public class CayleyDickson extends Object
Used to multiply hypercomplex numbers using the Cayley-Dickson algorithm, as well as compare Cayley-Dickson solutions, produces individual multiplication tables, sets of all tables of a given degree, and a recursive version for individual unit vectors

    • multiplyUnitHyperComplex

      public int multiplyUnitHyperComplex(int rootDegree, int row, int column, int cdz, int cdo)
      Multiplies two permuted Cayley-Dickson nion unit vectors. Wrapper function used to initiate the recursion when multiplying hypercomplex numbers. Initializes the factoradics.
      Parameters:
      rootDegree - hypercomplex degree, 2 = quaternions, 3 = octonions, 4 = sedonions, etc
      row - first hypercomplex unit vector factor
      column - second hypercomplex unit vector factor
      cdz - Cayley-Dickson permutation factoradic number, used in recursion on the way down
      cdo - Cayley-Dickson permutation factoradic number, used in recursion on the way up
      Returns:
      returns the result of multiplying two hypercomplex numbers row, column, with CD solution, cdz, cdo

    • multRecursive

      public int multRecursive(int rootDegree, int depth, int row, int column, int[] cdzRemainders, int[] cdoRemainders)
      The recursive function used to multiply two hypercomplex numbers
      Parameters:
      rootDegree - degree hypercomplex, 2 = quaternions, 3 = octonions, 4 = sedonions, etc
      depth - current depth of recursion
      row - first factor to be multiplied
      column - second factor to be multiplied
      cdzRemainders - the integer array of the factoradic of the permutation used on the way down in recursion
      cdoRemainders - the integer array of the factoradic of the permutation used on the way back up in recursion
      Returns:
      internal recursion result, returns the next step in rebuilding the hypercomplex number after having split it on the way down

    • cdCompare

      public int[][] cdCompare(int degree)
      Compares Cayley-Dickson solution hypercomplex multiplication tables, (cdz,cdo),(cdzz,cdoo), results in (cdz,cdzz) and (cdo,cdoo) each independently interacting in the same way as permutations of permutations

      This version checks all possible solutions

      Parameters:
      degree - hypercomplex degree number, quaternions = 2, octonions = 3, sedonions = 4
      Returns:
      a 2d int array of the interactions

    • cdCompareAgainstPoP

      public int[][] cdCompareAgainstPoP(int degree)
      Compares Cayley-Dickson solution hypercomplex multiplication tables, (cdz,cdo),(cdzz,cdoo), results in (cdz,cdzz),(cdo,cdoo) each independently interacting in the same way as permutations of permutations.

      This function is the same as cdCompare(), except that cdCompare() checks all possible solutions, and this function assumes the permutation composition interaction and outputs and error if it is not correct, and it doesn't output any errors as high as I've tested it. * chooses specific values to verify the permutation composition interchange, if this wasn't the case, error messages would print

      Parameters:
      degree - hypercomplex degree number, quaternions = 2, octonions = 3, sedonions = 4
      Returns:
      a 2d int array of the interactions

    • cdCompareAgainstPoPStochastic

      public int[][] cdCompareAgainstPoPStochastic(int degree)
      Compares Cayley-Dickson solution hypercomplex multiplication tables, (cdz,cdo),(cdzz,cdoo), results in (cdz,cdzz),(cdo,cdoo) each independently interacting in the same way as permutations of permutations.

      This function is the same as cdCompare(), except that cdCompare() checks all possible solutions, and this function chooses specific values at random locations to verify the permutation composition interchange, if this wasn't the case, error messages would print.

      This function exists because exhaustively checking every value at higher than sedonions takes prohibitively long.

      This function helps to verify the integrity of the permuted Cayley-Dickson multiplication tables because it is independently calculating permutations of permutations

      Parameters:
      degree - hypercomplex degree number, quaternions = 2, octonions = 3, sedonions = 4
      Returns:
      a 2d int array of the interactions

    • preCalculateTables

      public int[][][] preCalculateTables(int degree)
      Pre-calculates the entire set of multiplication tables of the permuted Cayley-Dickson quaternions, octonions, and sedonions. Pre-calculating beyond sedonions, O(n)=d!*d!*2^(2*d+1), blows up Java
      Parameters:
      degree - degree hypercomplex, 2 = quaternions, 3 = octonions, 4 = sedonions...
      Returns:
      an array of all permuted Cayley-Dickson multiplication tables for degree hypercomplex
